-- University Fee Limit Should Be Scrapped, Panel to Recommend, BBC Reports
-- B y   H o w a r d   M u s t o e
-- 2010-10-10T15:42:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-10/university-fee-limit-should-be-scrapped-panel-to-recommend-bbc-reports.html
U.K. universities should not have a
cap on the fees they charge, according to a report led by former
BP Plc Chief Executive Officer  John Browne , the British
Broadcasting Corp. reported, citing no-one.  Government support will only be guaranteed up to 7,000
pounds ($11,200) per year, the broadcaster reported, an increase
from the current tuition fee of 3,290 pounds per year. The
report is due to be delivered on Oct. 12, the broadcaster said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Howard Mustoe  in London at 
 hmustoe@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
